SIMPLE: unequal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unequal
<hw>Un*e"qual</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Inequal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not equal; not matched; not of
the same size, length, breadth, quantity, strength, talents,
acquirements, age, station, or the like; <as>as, the fingers are of
<ex>unequal</ex> length; peers and commoners are <ex>unequal</ex> in
rank</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Ill balanced or matched; disproportioned; hence, not
equitable; partial; unjust; unfair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Against <qex>unequal</qex> arms to fight in pain.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Jerome, a very <qex>unequal</qex> relator of the opinion of his
adversaries.</q> <rj><qau>John Worthington.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To punish me for what you make me do⟦br⟧
Seems much <qex>unequal</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not uniform; not equable; irregular; uneven; <as>as,
<ex>unequal</ex> pulsations; an <ex>unequal</ex> poem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Not adequate or sufficient; inferior; <as>as, the
man was <ex>unequal</ex> to the emergency; the timber was
<ex>unequal</ex> to the sudden strain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Not having the two sides or the
parts symmetrical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unequalable</ent>⟦br⟧
